Currently i have no Example. I will dig into.

If you execute the following Example you will see that the InvocationInfo is not set to the advanced function. The properties "MyCommand" and "InvocationName" of the InvocationInfo are Empty !

To set the InvocationInfo to $PSCmdlet.MyInvocation is one part of me suggestion.

```powershell
Function Get-ErrorHandling {

    [CmdletBinding()]
    Param()

    Process {
       Try {

              [double]::Parse('Hello')

       } Catch {

            $PSCmdlet.WriteError($_)
       }
    }
}

Get-ErrorHandling

$Error[0] | select -ExpandProperty InvocationInfo | select *

```
